Posted @withrepost • @dj_greg_wilson DISCOTHEQUE ARCHIVES – NEW EXTENDED HARDBACK
Delighted to announce that we’re now taking pre-orders for the new extended hardback version of Discotheque Archives. Pre-orders are scheduled for despatch next week, with UK delivery ahead of Christmas. Link in bio. 

Highlighting the pre-rave era, by focusing on the classic DJs, records, venues and labels that laid the groundwork on which a global dance culture was built, Discotheque Archives is now available as an extended hardback. It includes 20 extra sections, which fill in some of the gaps from the original series, and comes complete with a number of new Pete Fowler DJ illustrations and a comprehensive index that includes around 750 records referenced in the book’s pages.

Having originally unfurled as a monthly series for DJ Magazine, Discotheque Archives was first issued in book form two years ago, during lockdown, as a limited run paperback. The hope was that it would sell 250 copies, with a best-case scenario target of 500, but the response exceeded all expectations and the final amount swelled to 1600 in a matter of weeks. Putting a cap on things at that point, the intention has since been to extend the book - this new publication fulfilling that aim. 

All books will be dispatched via 1st class mail in secure wrap-around recyclable cardboard packaging (buyers also have a signed for option available). Three copies maximum per order, for larger amounts email info@superweirdsubstance.com.

#discothequearchives #gregwilson
